parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The insufficient capacity of the chassis can cause the springs to collapse, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The springs on the driver side of the motorhome collapse
the vehicle sags or leans to one side
the vehicle is difficult to handle or control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rusting screws on the trailer latch can cause the latch to fail, leading to trailer separation, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: Screws on the trailer latch are rusting
the trailer latch is loose or difficult to secure
the trailer is not properly attached to the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Defroster and Air Distribution System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the defroster and air distribution system can cause reduced visibility while driving, especially during inclement weather conditions, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The defroster does not work
the air conditioner must be turned on to get heat out of the vents
the door actuators do not switch to direct the air
inability to control air direction
and reduced airflow from the vents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracked exhaust manifolds can cause hot exhaust gases to escape, potentially leading to a fire hazard, and can also cause damage to surrounding components, such as wiring harnesses. In addition, broken manifold studs can make it difficult or impossible to repair the exhaust system.
symptoms: Cracking or breaking of exhaust manifold
broken manifold studs
melting of wiring harness due to hot exhaust
loud exhaust noise
decreased engine performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Wiring Harness Damage due to Exhaust Manifold Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Damage to the wiring harness can cause electrical system failures, leading to a range of problems, including engine stalling, loss of accessories, and even fires.
symptoms: Melting or burning of wiring harness
electrical system failures
engine stalling
loss of accessories.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension spring can cause the vehicle to lean or sag, leading to uneven weight distribution, reduced stability, and increased risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle leans or sags on one side
the spring collapses
the vehicle's ride height is uneven
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Overloading or improper weight distribution can cause excessive stress on the suspension components, leading to premature failure, reduced vehicle stability, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's ride height is uneven
the vehicle leans or sags on one side
the suspension components show signs of excessive wear
the vehicle's handling and stability are compromised.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate repair and maintenance can lead to further damage to the vehicle's suspension system, exacerbating the existing problem and potentially causing more severe consequences.
symptoms: The repair shop's proposed solution is inadequate or incomplete
the vehicle's condition worsens after repair
the repair shop fails to diagnose the underlying cause of the problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A transmission fluid leak can cause the transmission to overheat, leading to premature wear and eventual failure, which can result in costly repairs, loss of vehicle control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leaking from the transmission pan or lines
transmission fluid spots or stains under the vehicle
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission
difficulty shifting gears
slipping or hesitation when shifting gears.
